layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 39; written lines: 39; Uniform layout. Initial words in each section are written in larger characters. Catchwords are given on every page. Folio 1 is a title page.

history.provenance: Acquisition: Giuseppe Almanzi (b. 1801, d. 1860), bibliophile; his manuscript no. 293: his library including 322 medieval Hebrew manuscripts were purchased en bloc by the British Museum in October 1865 for £1,000 through Asher & Co., Berlin dealer to the British Museum (see 131-153: inscribed, folio [150v].
